name: An Zhao
description: Our objective in this paper is to push pedagogical theory and practice on to address more specifically the sorts of learning environments that are most likely to be relevant to the capacities needed for &ldquo;boundaryless careers&rdquo; &ndash; what we are calling border-crossing capacities. We do so by undertaking five main tasks. First, we demonstrate the increasing attention being paid by universities to the mix of capacities that future workers need for career success.
